<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1756</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Arthur Reynold</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt
                            of your telegram of March 14, 1917, requesting that the American
                            Minister at Peking endeavor to secure an extension of the time which
                            your representative may be permitted to make investigations in China and
                            conduct negotiations for a loan to the Chinese Government by your
                            bank.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have to advise you that the Chinese Minister has just informed
                            the Department that he telegraphed yesterday to Mr. J. J. Abbott, now en
                            route to Peking, that the extension had been granted.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>